THIRD-PARTY COMPONENTS
----------------------

This project bundles or makes use of the following third-party software and
services. Their respective licenses and terms apply to their own code.


1. tmi.js
   Source:  https://github.com/tmijs/tmi.js
   License: MIT License
   Used as: tmi.min.js (bundled) — Twitch Messaging Interface IRC client
   Copyright (c) 2015 Schmoopiie


2. Twitch API (Helix / PubSub)
   Source:  https://dev.twitch.tv
   Terms:   Twitch Developer Agreement
            https://www.twitch.tv/p/en/legal/developer-agreement/
   Used as: REST API calls (badges, cheermotes, channel points, user IDs) and
            PubSub WebSocket (channel point redemptions, raids, polls,
            predictions, hype train events)
   Note:    This project does not redistribute any Twitch code or assets.
            It accesses public Twitch APIs under their Developer Agreement.


3. 7TV
   Source:  https://7tv.app  /  https://github.com/SevenTV
   Terms:   7TV Terms of Service — https://7tv.app/legal/tos
   Used as: REST API (emotes, user cosmetics, badges, paints) and
            EventSub WebSocket (wss://events.7tv.io/v3) for live updates
   Note:    This project does not redistribute any 7TV code or assets.
            Emote images are served directly from the 7TV CDN (cdn.7tv.app).


4. BetterTTV (BTTV)
   Source:  https://betterttv.com  /  https://github.com/night/betterttv
   Terms:   BetterTTV Terms of Service — https://betterttv.com/terms
   Used as: REST API (global and channel emotes)
   Note:    This project does not redistribute any BTTV code or assets.
            Emote images are served directly from the BTTV CDN (cdn.betterttv.net).


5. FrankerFaceZ (FFZ)
   Source:  https://www.frankerfacez.com  /  https://github.com/FrankerFaceZ
   Terms:   FrankerFaceZ Terms of Service — https://www.frankerfacez.com/p/tos
   Used as: REST API (global emotes, channel emotes, FFZ badges)
   Note:    This project does not redistribute any FFZ code or assets.
            Emote images are served directly from the FFZ CDN (cdn.frankerfacez.com).


6. Chatterino
   Source:  https://chatterino.com  /  https://github.com/Chatterino/chatterino2
   License: MIT License
   Terms:   https://github.com/Chatterino/chatterino2/blob/master/LICENSE
   Used as: Public badge API (https://api.chatterino.com/badges) for community
            Chatterino badges displayed next to usernames.
   Note:    This project does not redistribute any Chatterino code or assets.
